Parlimentary Spokesperson, Moloto Mothapo says they are ready for the formal program to start ahead of the first  State of the Nation Address (Sona) of the sixth administration. Mothapo says they are expecting more than 1 200 guest to attend the sixth Parliament’s first Sona. See prep gallery below:  Invited guests are expected to start arriving on the red carpet at around 15h30. Former presidents, Thabo Mbeki and Kgalema Motlanthe have also confirmed their attendance. Struggle stalwarts Andrew Mlangeni and Dennis Goldberg – the two surviving Rivonia trialists – together with 1956 Women’s march heroines Sophie de Bruyn and Gertrude Shope, will also be attending. The President is expected to arrive at about 18h30 with his address starting at 19h00. For more on this, watch Moloto Mothapo below:  You can watch the State of the Nation address live on sabcnews.com 